Package: SCdetMito
Title: Data-Driven Mitochondrial Cutoff Detection for Single-Cell
        RNA-Seq Quality Control
Version: 1.3.5
Authors@R: person("Silu Hu", email = "erichu121@foxmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides utilities for single-cell RNA-seq quality control with
    a focus on mitochondrial content. The package estimates recommended
    mitochondrial cutoffs from retained-cell profiles and interval-specific
    retention-loss enrichment, performs
    one-sample or multi-sample QC, supports group-aware cutoff strategies for
    integrated studies, optional doublet removal, and generates QC summary
    tables, plots, and benchmark outputs.
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports: ggplot2, reshape2, rlang, Seurat
Suggests: DoubletFinder, knitr, rmarkdown, testthat (>= 3.0.0)
